   Up Arrow to Map   1. Mike's Beach Resort

        Waterbody: Hood Canal
        Site Manager: Mikes Beach Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                               Boat Launch Type:

                                 1 Concrete Ramp
                                 1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     8 Paved and Striped Spaces

                               Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                 2 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Quilcene, S on US 101 22 mi to milepost 317.5; L to resort.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a few holes developing in the concrete. The resort
        also has a small campground, waterfront cabins, convenience store,
        and dormitory rooms. The resort caters to tourist, shell fish
        harvesters, and diving groups.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Lake Cushman State Park

        Waterbody: Lake Cushman
        Site Manager: State Parks
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            3 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            48 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - the park is closed during winter months.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Hoodsport, W on SR 119, 7 mi to Lake Cushman State Park.
        Site Description:

        The ramps at Lake Cushman State Park consist of two longer ramps and
        one short ramp. The boat ramps have a moderate grade with adequate
        traction. Concrete planks are broken and chipped resulting in
        exposed re-bar. The gravel from between the planks has washed away
        exposing the steel fasteners. There are abrupt edges on the side of
        the ramps and some erosion beginning to undermine the sides. No
        designated disabled parking. Lake Cushman State Park also has
        campsites, R.V. dump station, picnic area, and a public phone.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. Lake Cushman Resort

        Waterbody: Lake Cushman
        Site Manager: Lake Cushman Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Shower
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - cannot use the boat ramp when the reservoir is drawn down past
        the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        In Hoodsport, W on SR 119 4.5 mi; L to resort.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade with adequate traction.
        The ramp appears to have been newly constructed. The ramp is out of
        the water when the reservoir is drawn down. Drainage from the
        hillside runs along the side of the boat ramp. The facilities are
        for the patron of the resort with an additional fee to use the ramp.
        A convenience store and play area are located next to the boat ramp.
        The resort also offers picnic tables, fire-rings, rental cabins, and
        boat and jet ski rentals. The resort is open year-round.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Cushman Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Lake Kokanee
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            75 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Hoodsport, W on SR 119 2.7 mi; L on Cushman-Potlatch Rd, go .8
        mi; R on Lower Lake Rd, go .3 mi; at bottom of hill, first L to
        ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade. Several of the concrete planks at
        the shoreline are broken to some extent. Gravel has washed away from
        between the planks exposing the steel fasteners. A private park is
        located next to the access site. A well has recently been installed
        at the east end of the parking area. The WDFW sign has been knocked
        over at the launching area.


   Up Arrow to Map   5. Hood Canal Recreational Park

        Waterbody: The Great Bend
        Site Manager: Tacoma Public Utilities
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     40 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            60 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Olympia, N on US 101 32 mi. Across from Tacoma City Light's
        Cushman No. 2 Hydroelectric Plant, turn R.
        Site Description:

        This boat ramp has a moderate grade and adequate traction. The
        concrete is cracked and has required patching in the past. Wire
        reinforcement along the side of the ramp is breaking apart. The Hood
        Canal Recreational Park is a day-use facility that also offers
        picnic tables, fire-rings, beach access for swimming, and a public
        phone. No overnight parking or camping. No designated disabled
        parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   6. Skokomish River - Smith (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Skokomish River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - difficult to effectively launch when river level is high or
        low.

        Driving Directions:

        From Shelton, N on US101; cross Skokomish River, go .5 mi,then turn
        L on Sunnyside Rd, go 1.5 mi. L to access site.
        Site Description:

        There is evidence that boaters have been using a gravel bar to
        launch from, but a formal ramp is nonexistent. The access to the
        river from the parking lot is a rough and uneven road. The site has
        received flood water in the past. The access site is most likely to
        be used by drift boats than sleds, but there are indications of
        possible motorized usage. Vandalism (graffiti) on the WDFW sign and
        vault toilet. No designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   7. Nahwatzel Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Nahwatzel Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From US 101 at Matlock exit, W 10.6 mi on Shelton-Matlock Rd; Just
        before store, turn R to access site.
        Site Description:

        The concrete planks have been undermined by erosion and have caused
        planks to break. The ramp surface is uneven. Steel fasteners and
        re-bar are exposed. The vault toilets are the "round' fiberglass
        units.


   Up Arrow to Map   8. Shafer State Park

        Waterbody: East Fork - Satsop River
        Site Manager: State Parks
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     40 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            7 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Satsop, N on E Satsop Rd 8.2 mi to Shafer State Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat access site has a gentle grade and is located on a section
        of river with a moderate to swift current. Shafer State Park also
        has picnic shelters, barbecue grills, flush restrooms, public phone,
        picnic tables, and trails nearby. Across the road from the day-use
        are is the campground area with more restrooms.


