   Up Arrow to Map   11. Arcadia Point Public Boat Ramp

        Waterbody: Totten Inlet
        Site Manager: Squaxin Island Tribe
        Nearest City: Shelton


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Olympia, N on US 101 15 mi; R (east) on Lynch Rd, go 9.5 mi to
        ramp at end of Rd.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade with adequate traction.
        The concrete slab has a few cracks, but none represent any apparent
        structural damage. Abrupt edges on both sides of the ramp. The
        parking area is about 300 feet away from the boat ramp.


   Up Arrow to Map   12. Shorecrest Park

        Waterbody: Hammersley Inlet
        Site Manager: Mason County Parks & Rec
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            1 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Shelton, N on SR3 6 mi; At milepost 9, turn R on Agate Rd &
        follow to its end. At stop sign, turn R onto Crestview and go 3 mi;
        At end of Crestview, turn R on E Parkway Blvd and go 100 ft; Turn R
        on Shorecrest Park Way & go 500 ft to boat ramp
        Site Description:

        In addition to the boat ramp, there are also a lawn area, a picnic
        table, and park bench at this park. Parking is very limited.
        Additional parking can be found along roadside. No overnight camping
        permitted.


   Up Arrow to Map   13. Shelton Boat Ramp

        Waterbody: Oakland Bay
        Site Manager: Shelton Port of
        Nearest City: Shelton


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Shelton, N on SR 3, .25 mi; just past yellow railroad bridge, R
        to large gravel parking area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade and is on a firm natural gravel
        surface of the bay. The ramp location provides protection from
        weather and tidal influences. A marine rail car for a commercial
        marine boat maintenance business operates next to the ramp. Adjacent
        to the ramp is a moorage facility for yachts. No other amenities,
        beyond parking and ramp, exist at this site.


