   Up Arrow to Map   15. Latimer's Landing

        Waterbody: Pickering Passage
        Site Manager: Mason County Parks & Rec
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Shelton, NE on SR 3 8 mi; R (east) on Pickering Rd, go 3.2 mi;
        site on L just before Hartstene Island Bridge.
        Site Description:

        This boat ramp has a moderate grade. This location experiences
        moderate tidal currents. The concrete panels are placed lengthwise
        on the lower section of the ramp giving the ramp an uneven surface.
        This site is the only access on saltwater around Hartstene Island.


   Up Arrow to Map   16. Phillips Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Phillips Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp
                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            30 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Shelton, NE on SR 3 8 mi; R (east) on Pickering Rd, go 1.1 mi;
        R on Phillips Lake Rd, go 1 mi; L on Phillips Lake Loop Rd, go 200
        ft., R to access site. T
        Site Description:

        The gravel between the concrete planks has washed away resulting in
        exposed fasteners. The sides of the ramp are beginning to develop
        undermining erosion. The front of the ramp has an abrupt edge.
        Debris from past storms has been dumped at this site. The remains of
        a dock rests on the shore at this site. No designated disabled
        parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   17. Spencer Lake Resort

        Waterbody: Spencer Lake
        Site Manager: Spencer Lake Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can
     Water Available

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Asphalt Ramp
                                   1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     52 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Shelton, N on SR 3 8 mi; E 1 mi on Pickering Rd; ramp on R.
        Site Description:

        The asphalt ramp has a gentle grade that eventually turns to gravel
        near the shoreline. The gravel portion of the ramp is even. The sign
        at the ramp states "No Public Access", but the owners do allow the
        public to launch. A restaurant and tavern are located next to the
        boat ramp area. Parking for the resort is across Pickering Road from
        the boat ramp. R.V. campsites with full hook-ups and a picnic area
        are located behind the parking area.


   Up Arrow to Map   18. Spencer Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Spencer Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp
                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     20 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            60 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Shelton, NE on SR 3 8 mi; R on Pickering Rd, go .2 mi; R on
        Spencer Lake Rd; go 1.1 mi; access site on L.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. The gravel between the
        planks has washed away exposing the steel fasteners. Abrupt edges
        are present on both sides of the ramp with undermining erosion
        occurring on the left side. The gravel area to the right side of the
        ramp appears to be used frequently by boaters for launching and
        loading. No designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   19. Limerick Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Limerick Lake
