   Up Arrow to Map   21. Twanoh State Park

        Waterbody: Hood Canal
        Site Manager: State Parks
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Fuel Available

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   2 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     15 Paved Spaces, No Striping

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   30 Paved Spaces, No Striping

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, S on SR 3, 1 mi; R on SR 106, go 8 mi; at W end of
        park, turn R to boat ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. Traction is hindered
        however by algae growth on the surface. There is evidence of past
        damage from the different concrete patches scattered around the
        ramp. Twanoh State Park also offers lawn areas, picnic tables,
        barbecue grills, a picnic shelter, fire rings, and camp sites. There
        is a fee to use the boat ramp. Additional parking can be found
        across SR106 from the boat ramp area. The camping areas and some of
        the parking lots are closed during the winter months. The boat ramp
        and parking area remains open throughout the year.


   Up Arrow to Map   22. Mason Lake Park & Boat Launch

        Waterbody: Mason Lake
        Site Manager: Mason County Parks & Rec
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Loading Float
                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     4 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            28 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, SW on SR 106 7 mi; L on Trails Rd, go 3.5 mi; R on
        Mason Lake Drive W, go .5 mi; L to boat ramp area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. Planks have previously
        been repaired. Abrupt edges and undermining erosion occur on the
        sides of the boat ramp. Steel fasteners are exposed and corroding.
        Picnic tables and a small lawn area are located near the boat ramp
        area. The restrooms are closed from November through March.


   Up Arrow to Map   23. Fairharbor Boat Ramp

        Waterbody: Case Inlet
        Site Manager: Grapeview Port of
        Nearest City: Grapeview


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   2 Concrete Ramp
                                   1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     6 Gravel Spaces

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   19 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, S on SR 3, 7 mi; L (east) on Grapeview Rd, go 4 mi; L
        on Grapeview Loop Rd, go .5 mi. R at "Public Boat Launch" sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and traction is hindered by algae
        on the surface. Next to the boat ramp is a private marina that has a
        convenience store, fuel, and boat moorage that may be available for
        public use. Near the ramp is a small grass area with beach access.
        The owner of Fairharbor Marina complained about the no overnight
        parking issue in the boat ramp parking area. He states that it has
        become an inconvenience to his business.


