   Up Arrow to Map   27. Howell Lake Campground and Picnic Area

        Waterbody: Howell Lake
        Site Manager: Natural Resources Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - campground is closed during the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, W on SR 300 3.8 mi; R , go 4 mi to NE Belfair-Tahuya
        Rd; at 'Y', continue on Belfair-Tahuya Rd another 2 mi; turn L at
        Howell Lake Camp; Picnic Area sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade. Erosion is present on the upper
        ramp due to parking lot drainage. The campground has ten campsites
        and a picnic area. An accessible vault toilet is located near the
        entrance to the campground. Drinking water is also available near
        the entrance to the campground.


