                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            7 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, W on SR 300 (becomes N Shore Rd) 12 mi. R on
        Belfair-Tahuya Rd, go 4 mi; L on NE Dewatto Rd, go .25 mi; R on NE
        Tee Lake Rd; go 1 mi to "Public Fishing" sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade. Drainage from the parking area is
        creating ruts in the ramp approach and boat ramp. Drainage from the
        entry road is also creating ruts in the road into the access area,


   Up Arrow to Map   29. Menards Landing

        Waterbody: Hood Canal
        Site Manager: Tahuya Port of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, W 17 mi on SR 300. Site on L just before Rendsl; Creek
        bridge.
        Site Description:

        This ramp is a hand launch only site and is well protected in a
        cove. The bank cut is reinforced with rock retaining walls. The
        parking for the park is across the street in a gravel lot. The park
        also has concrete picnic tables and a large gazebo structure. The
        entire park surface is loose gravel that can be difficult for some
        to traverse. Large landscaping rocks drastically narrowing the path
        from the park to the boat ramp area making it inaccessible for some
        visitors. No designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   30. Robbins Lake (DNR)

        Waterbody: Robbins Lake
        Site Manager: Natural Resources Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     6 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            4 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, W 12 mi on SR 300; R on Belfair-Tahuya Rd, go 4 mi; L
        on Dewatto Rd, go 2 mi; L on gravel Rd; go .5 mi; L on Hahobas
        Drive; go .5 mi; R on Hahobas Lane; ramp at 'T'.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade. Drainage from the
        parking area has begun to erode the ramp. Picnic areas with
        fire-ring are also at this site. Camp Habobas property boundaries
        surround the boat ramp and picnic area and are off limits to public
        entry.


   Up Arrow to Map   31. Aldrich Lake-P. Sharp (DNR)

