   Up Arrow to Map   33. Wooten Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Wooten Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            40 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Belfair, W on SR 300 3.8 mi; R on Belfair-Tahuya Rd, go 5.5 mi;
        L on Haven Lake Drive 1.6 mi to access site.
        Site Description:

        The gravel between the planks at the waterline and below has washed
        away. The ramp is uneven. Several planks are broken or cracked.
        Abrupt edges are present on both sides of the ramp. No overnight
        camping or parking. No designated disabled parking. Garbage has been
        dumped around the restroom area.


